---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="SocialProof vs Reviewflowz — Testimonial Tool Comparison | SocialProof" description="Reviewflowz aggregates review data from Google, Capterra, and G2. SocialProof collects first-party testimonials and displays them. Here's how to decide." canonical="https://socialproof.dev/vs/reviewflowz">
<style>
    body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; margin: 0; background: #fff; color: #111; }
    nav { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; padding: 1rem 2rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee; }
    nav a.logo { font-weight: 800; font-size: 1.25rem; color: #111; text-decoration: none; }
    nav .nav-links a { margin-left: 1.5rem; color: #555; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; }
    nav .cta-nav { background: #111; color: #fff !important; padding: .45rem 1rem; border-radius: 6px; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 4rem 2rem 2rem; max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
    .vs-badge { display: inline-block; background: #f0f0f0; color: #555; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: .06em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: .35rem .75rem; border-radius: 99px; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); font-weight: 800; line-height: 1.15; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
    .hero h1 span { color: #4f46e5; }
    .hero p { font-size: 1.15rem; color: #444; max-width: 560px; margin: 0 auto 2rem; }
    .hero-cta { display: inline-block; background: #4f46e5; color: #fff; padding: .85rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-size: 1rem; }
    .hero-cta:hover { background: #3730a3; }
    .price-callout { display: inline-flex; gap: 2rem; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px solid #e5e5e5; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    .price-callout .item { text-align: center; }
    .price-callout .item .price { font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 800; }
    .price-callout .item .label { font-size: 0.85rem; color: #777; margin-top: .2rem; }
    .price-callout .item.vouch .price { color: #4f46e5; }
    .price-callout .item.other .price { color: #dc2626; }
    section { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3rem 2rem; }
    h2 { font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .compare-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .compare-table th { padding: .75rem 1rem; text-align: left; font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .05em; color: #888; border-bottom: 2px solid #eee; }
    .compare-table th:nth-child(2) { color: #4f46e5; }
    .compare-table td { padding: .85rem 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #f0f0f0; font-size: 0.97rem; vertical-align: top; }
    .compare-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
    .compare-table td:first-child { color: #555; font-weight: 500; }
    .yes { color: #16a34a; font-weight: 600; }
    .no { color: #dc2626; font-weight: 600; }
    .partial { color: #d97706; font-weight: 600; }
    .winner-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .winner-card { border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.75rem; }
    .winner-card.vouch { background: #f0fdf4; border: 1px solid #86efac; }
    .winner-card.other { background: #fafafa; border: 1px solid #e5e5e5; }
    .winner-card h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 .75rem; }
    .winner-card ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; }
    .winner-card li { font-size: 0.92rem; color: #444; margin-bottom: .4rem; }
    .savings-box { background: #fffbeb; border: 1px solid #fcd34d; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; text-align: center; }
    .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid #f0f0f0; padding: 1.25rem 0; }
    .faq-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .faq-item h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 .5rem; }
    .faq-item p { font-size: 0.95rem; color: #555; margin: 0; }
    .cta-section { text-align: center; background: #f5f3ff; border-radius: 16px; padding: 3rem 2rem; margin: 3rem 0; }
    footer { text-align: center; padding: 2rem; color: #999; font-size: 0.85rem; border-top: 1px solid #eee; }
    footer a { color: #999; text-decoration: none; margin: 0 .75rem; }
    @media (max-width: 640px) { .price-callout { flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; } .winner-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>
<nav>
    <a href="/" class="logo">SocialProof</a>
    <div class="nav-links">
        <a href="/vs/">Comparisons</a>
        <a href="/#pricing">Pricing</a>
        <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev" class="cta-nav">Try Free</a>
    </div>
</nav>

<div class="hero">
    <span class="vs-badge">SocialProof vs Reviewflowz</span>
    <h1>Aggregating reviews is great.<br><span>Owning your testimonials</span> is better.</h1>
    <p>Reviewflowz monitors and aggregates your reviews from Google, G2, and Capterra. SocialProof collects direct testimonials from your customers and displays them on your site. Different tools, different jobs — here's how to choose.</p>
    <div class="price-callout">
        <div class="item vouch">
            <div class="price">Free</div>
            <div class="label">SocialProof — free forever for 1 active widget</div>
        </div>
        <div class="item other">
            <div class="price">$49/mo</div>
            <div class="label">Reviewflowz — starts at $49/mo</div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev" class="hero-cta">Start free with SocialProof →</a>
</div>

<section>
    <h2>Two different approaches to social proof</h2>
    <p><strong>Reviewflowz</strong> is a review monitoring and Slack notification tool. It watches your profiles on G2, Capterra, Google, and other platforms, then alerts you when new reviews come in and provides analytics dashboards. It's primarily a B2B SaaS tool for tracking what people say about you across the internet.</p>
    <p><strong>SocialProof</strong> is a testimonial collection and display platform. You send your customers a collection form, they submit their testimonials, you approve them, and they go live on your website automatically. Your visitors see real customer words right where it matters.</p>

    <table class="compare-table">
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Feature</th>
                <th>SocialProof</th>
                <th>Reviewflowz</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>Primary function</td>
                <td class="yes">Collect + display website testimonials</td>
                <td>Monitor 3rd-party review sites</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Embeddable website widget</td>
                <td class="yes">Yes — one line of code</td>
                <td class="no">Not the primary use case</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Collect first-party testimonials</td>
                <td class="yes">Yes — built-in collection forms</td>
                <td class="no">Monitors existing reviews only</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Slack / email review alerts</td>
                <td class="no">Not a feature</td>
                <td class="yes">Yes — core feature</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Review analytics dashboard</td>
                <td class="partial">Basic approval workflow</td>
                <td class="yes">Yes — sentiment trends, volume</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Testimonial moderation</td>
                <td class="yes">Full approval control</td>
                <td class="partial">Read-only monitoring</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Works without G2/Capterra presence</td>
                <td class="yes">Yes — direct collection</td>
                <td class="no">Needs 3rd-party profiles</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Good for service businesses</td>
                <td class="yes">Yes — built for them</td>
                <td class="partial">Better for B2B SaaS</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Free plan</td>
                <td class="yes">Free forever for 1 widget</td>
                <td class="no">No free plan</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Starting price</td>
                <td class="yes">Free / $9/mo Pro</td>
                <td class="no">$49/mo</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Who each tool is for</h2>
    <div class="winner-grid">
        <div class="winner-card vouch">
            <h3>SocialProof is ideal for:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Small businesses and service providers</li>
                <li>Anyone without a G2 or Capterra profile</li>
                <li>Businesses wanting reviews on their own website</li>
                <li>Early-stage companies building trust from scratch</li>
                <li>Shopify sellers, freelancers, local service businesses</li>
                <li>Anyone who wants free-to-start pricing</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="winner-card other">
            <h3>Reviewflowz is ideal for:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>B2B SaaS companies with G2/Capterra presence</li>
                <li>Companies managing reviews across many platforms</li>
                <li>Customer success teams monitoring sentiment</li>
                <li>Businesses needing Slack alerts for new reviews</li>
                <li>Enterprise teams with dedicated review management budgets</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="savings-box">
        <strong>$49/mo vs free.</strong><br>
        If you're a small business wanting to display testimonials on your website, you don't need Reviewflowz's monitoring infrastructure. SocialProof is built for your use case and starts free.
    </div>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Can you use both?</h2>
    <p>Yes — and some businesses do. If you're a B2B SaaS company that wants to monitor your G2 reviews <em>and</em> display first-party testimonials on your landing page, using Reviewflowz alongside SocialProof makes sense. They do genuinely different jobs.</p>
    <p>But if you're a small business, consultant, or local service provider who just wants to turn happy customers into website social proof — SocialProof is the only tool you need, and it's free to start.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
    <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Does SocialProof import reviews from Google or G2?</h3>
        <p>Currently SocialProof focuses on first-party testimonials collected directly from your customers. This gives you full control over the content and presentation. Google review import is on the roadmap.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What if I want both review monitoring and a website widget?</h3>
        <p>Start with SocialProof (free) for your website testimonials. If you grow to a point where you need to monitor your G2/Capterra presence, Reviewflowz can complement SocialProof for that specific use case.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Is SocialProof only for website embedding?</h3>
        <p>SocialProof's primary job is collection + display. You get a shareable collection form link (send it to customers), an approval dashboard, and an embeddable widget. It's end-to-end testimonial management, not review monitoring.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What's SocialProof's free plan?</h3>
        <p>Free forever for 1 active widget — unlimited testimonials collected and displayed. No credit card required. Pro is $9/mo for multiple widgets, custom branding removal, and priority support.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<div class="cta-section" style="max-width:900px; margin: 0 auto 3rem;">
    <h2>Your customers are already saying great things</h2>
    <p>Give them a way to say it on your website — and let it convert your next customer.</p>
    <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev" class="hero-cta">Start free with SocialProof →</a>
</div>

<footer>
    <a href="/">SocialProof</a>
    <a href="/vs/">All Comparisons</a>
    <a href="/#pricing">Pricing</a>
    <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev">Sign Up Free</a>
    <br><br>© 2025 SocialProof. All rights reserved.
</footer>

